items.name: Maki Harukawa - Danganronpa v3
items.description:
What does it do you ask?

All of the Danganronpa's are great games with great characters, so there is a bunch of them that I want to do eventually. First off, is Maki Harukawa from Danganronpa 3 and, without going too much into spoiler land, she's fun (and obviously cute). And can actually stand-up to herself against anyone wants to push back against her.

How to use it:

(I use Sampling Method DPM++ SDE Karras and Upscaler R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B).

0.6 to 1 depending on model/lora/etc combination.

Main Trigger

MakiH - Base tag to get Maki.

red thighhighs - Because it screws this up sometimes.

Other Useful Tags

Whatever else you want!

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1-3: Hasaku with just this Lora.

4: MistoonAnime with just this Lora.

5: RevAnimated with just this Lora.

6: DreamShaper with just this Lora.

8: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Courtesan Locon.

8: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Stripper Locon.

8: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Naughty Nurse Locon.

8: Hasaku combo'd with my released Biker Locon.

8: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress Being Eaten Locon.

How was it trained?

It was trained on animefull_final with 35 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging and a wide range of different images. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

What's next for this?

Should be good!

What's next that isn't this?

More character Loras. (Freya from Danmachi, Mio and Ushio from Summertime Render, Miu and Junko and Kaede from Danganronpa, Akane Shinjo from SSSS. Gridman, Manon from Street Fighter, Yuna Yunis from Legendary Hero is Dead, Kanzaki Kaori from the Railgun Series, Jill Valentine from Resident Evil, Rupee from Nikke, Spectre Tenebria from E7, Zephia from Fire Emblem Engage, Ivy from Soul Calibur 5, Heine from Combatants Will Be Dispatched, Conqueror Lilias from E7, Evelynn from LoL (base version), Laharl-Chan from Disgaea 5, Miku from Idaten Deities, Kasumi from P5, Ikumi Mito from Food Wars, Alice Nakiri from Food Wars, Lulu from FF10, Dominique de Sade from Vanitas, and Dos from One Punch Man.) And maybe Wilhelm van Astrea, my favorite Re:Zero husbando or a Prinny from Disgaea.

V2's of some of the previous Loras. Specifically make them more diversely acceptable with other models and LORA's.

I also have some more quite NSFW Locon's. I decided to list them as well, so if people have preferences on which to fix up first let me know. Specifically, Foot Worship, Head Infected, Living Clothes, Masturbating while Clothed (I had trouble getting masturbation with clothes on, so making a Locon), Sex Doll, Slutify/Hookerify, Shy Gal-ify (I had no idea this was a thing but I found so many images of it when looking at other stuff I just tossed it in), Bowsette Transformation (Makes your waifu kinda look like Bowsette without changing other aspects), Fallen Angel, Pony Bondage (specifically with the capability of being "riden"), X-ray Vision (glasses that give you x-ray vision of a girl, this one has been hard), Vore (Waifu mid-way being eaten specifically), More Brainwashing (in ideation for this still), Bound Yuri (two girls tied up, breast to breast and likely kissing), Tied Till Orgasm (basically the waifu tied up with vibrators and being overwhelmed with pleasure), Beta Censorship (Automatically censors any images you create to make them BetaSafe), being stepped on, Robotification, Tentacles, Pillory, Latex Corruption, Combat Drone (hard to describe but basically making them a mindless sci-fi combat warrior), JAV Supervillain, and Blacked.

And, uh, I want to make a few SFW Locon's so I have a Sailor, Courtesan, Egyptian, Stripper, Naughty Schoolgirl, Witch, Pirate, Samurai, Tomboy, Ninja, Maid, forest fairy, barbarian.

I'm also planning to split up my Evil-ify your Waifu into two separate files, Lustful Corruption and Pure Evil.

Or just give me some random suggestion or priority opinions. That works too.

Twitter is here if you have any ideas you want to toss over (also feel free to do it in jus the comments here too).-> https://twitter.com/TwoMoreTimes89.

items.name: Jessica Alba (LoRA SDXL 1.0)
items.description:
Although it began with some kind of experiment it's getting closer to desired results, despite of the fact that there is a great range of improvement in base model, especially regarding weird limbs or hands (yes, it's still there!! :( ) Anyway I'm satisfied with this model, waiting for a future improved photorealistic checkpoints based on SDXL base 1.0.

LoRA weights should be between 1.1 and 1.4 in my experience (but you're free to test)

For portraits you can use 896 x 1152, 768 x 1344, 832 x 1216, 640 x 1536 or even 768x1024 resolutions.

This LoRa has been trained after carefully selecting 74 images. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.

items.name: Kate Beckinsale (JG)
items.description:
Kate Beckinsale is a British actress and model, mainly known for her roles in the Underwold series of films and other movies such as Pearl Harbor or The Aviator.

140-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (k4t3b3ck:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Hair over one eye, both eyes, LECO
items.description:
This model is LECO, LECO is used same way as LORA.

Model fixes the issue of bad hair over one eye / both eyes.

With weight 1-2.5 you will get hair over one eye, it depends on several factors like model and how long your prompt is how much weight you have to use.

With weight of 3-4+ you usually get hair over both of your eyes. Test around the weight. Weight can go to +7 and have decent image. More weight changes the composition and might give random effects like double colored hair and stuff.

It can slightly alter composition.

With negative weight the image is really random. Very often food is involved in some strange way.

items.name: FoolKat GOD-OF-SEDUCTION
items.description:
This is the nineteenth, and most-likely, final model in my GOD-OF series. I am currently working on a GODDESS-OF series that involves 3D/2.5D images instead of anime/cartoon themed images. Look forward to it!

You can find all the models at GOD-OF-GREED, GOD-OF-ENVY, GOD-OF-LOVE, GOD-OF-ANIME, GOD-OF-LUST, GOD-OF-JUSTICE, GOD-OF-TIME, GOD-OF-FANTASY, GOD-OF-JOY, GOD-OF-HORROR, GOD-OF-PRIDE, GOD-OF-PUNK, GOD-OF-STORMS, GOD-OF-EUPHORIA, GOD-OF-GLUTTONY, GOD-OF-THE-WEST, GOD-OF-BEAUTY, GOD-OF-SEDUCTION, and GOD-OF-PEACE.

This model was a happy accident that occurred while making my GOD-OF-GLUTTONY model. I wasn't able to get the furry aesthetic I was going for in that particular model, but I did succeed in making a model with rounded edges on the models that made them look more realistic and sensual, hence the SEDUCTION part of the model name.

The model has Blessed2 VAE baked into it, so no VAE required.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: Guyver_cha
items.description:
Note:

For v15:

It feels like that the model can't tell the difference between 3 G units, so just ust "g01" for the best result. if I can find more individual (and sorted) data for the specific character, I'll retain it.

The AptomFrost has the same problem, but it is over fitting rather than not showing up ;D.

Now the Guyver looks more authentic thanks to my computer spending whole night reading the classic manga novel.

Now it must fall in love with the story and characters, and wants to continue the legend.

======================================================================================================================

When using to generate Guyver, you can use full strength.

When generate AptomFrost, use at lower strength, that part of model is overfit...

I've changed trigger word to g00, g01, g02f, g03, aptomf, so it has no conflict with models' key words. Use helmet and bodysuit to enhance your result if the model don't know what to do.

Using at full strength to get Guyver, lower strength to get Guyver's costume.

Using the lora alone without trigger word to get retro colored img.

===========================================================

===========================================================

Childhood obsession, never ending story.

I did try multiple times and got no idea why it is so hard to train...

Maybe just because I don't have a good dataset.

Mainly was trained on the model pictures, some manga covers. Maybe I should try to use the manga pages too?

items.name: Soggy Skeletons (XL Style/Char LORA)
items.description:
First time training anything, started creating some random images on an app and really liked where things went so thought I would train a model based on the images. It basically generates images of skeletal figures in a rainy/wet setting in a cartoony or painted style. This is a very odd and specific theme so I'm not sure many people will like it. It was only trained on images of feminine/female figures, I used a tutorial to train it and have not tested it 100% thoroughly.

Sample prompt:

portrait shot of (ssk skel), hdhq <lora:SskSkel-v1:0.3>

Sample settings:

sd_xl_base_1.0 checkpoint, DPM++ 2M Karras or Euler A, 25-30 steps, cfg 7-9, clipskip 2-4, 1024x1024 or 832x1216 or 1216x832

I'm not sure if hi res fix or i2i refiner is needed as it seems to produce what I was going for but feel free to experiment and use it however

items.name: Gerph Artstyle
items.description:
Lora imitating the style of the artist Gerph

best prompts: 1girl, solo, breasts, outline

Work better with AOM (AbyssOrangeMix) models or merge, but can do fine with any anime model.

Letting the weight of the model at 1 can work if you don't have hands on the images, else it may give some strange results. Thats why I suggest you set the weigth at 0.9 or 0.8, and if it still give bad hands, try to describe the position of the hands in the prompts (clenched hands, v sign, ...)

If you want to add a loras or embeddings in the prompt, try to lower their weight (especially for embeddings)

Like all my other style models, faces can also turn out a little strange, so you will need to do some inpainting (with the parameter "only masked") to have the best result.

If you manage to have some great results or if you want to suggest some improvement for the model, you can send me reviews or feedbacks in the comment.

items.name: Pee-Wee Herman
items.description:
Pee-wee Herman is a fictional character created and performed by comedian and actor Paul Reubens (1952-2023). Pee-wee began as a character in the L.A. comedy troupe The Groundlings in 1977, and he took off soon after: an HBO special in 1981, the movie Pee-wee's Big Adventure in 1985, the children's series "Pee-wee's Playhouse" for five years, and another film, Big Top Pee-Wee, in 1988.

This embedding is based on 30 images, cooked for a total of 300 steps on base SD1.5 â€” 16 vectors per token, a 0.004 learning rate, a batch size of 6, and 5 gradient steps.

This one came out a little odd, though I'm happy with it. It wants to make Pee-wee into a late 1940s/early 1950s TV star, maybe on the DuMont Network. Edward R. Murrow's deputy editor. The company man keeping a secret on the LIRR. More The Man in the Gray Flannel Suit than the wild child of 1980s Saturday morning television. He's even a little hunky at times. Anyway, R.I.P. Paul Reubens.

items.name: On/Off LoRA for SDXL
items.description:
This is an On/Off LoRA trained for SDXL 1.0. It should work on SDXL-based checkpoints. This first version was trained at 640x640 (with bucketing up to 1024) and seems to produce good results at 768x768.

Precede your prompt with the keyword "onoff" and for best results also include a phrase such as "side by side photo" and/or "split screen" in your prompt to facilitate the composition, then describe the subject and their clothing. (Note that the text encoder is fundamentally different in SDXL so the keyword on its own may be useless.)

If you're working with SD1.5 or a derivative checkpoint, there is already a LoRA for that.

items.name: Gloria Sato Big City Greens
items.description:
I made this model using Seaart AI's Lora training function. I have no idea how this really came out compared to the one's I've used Google collab to make, since the Lora training function does not have much information on how to configurate the more advanced settings. The only tutorials I found is the one they have on the Seaart AI subreddit and the other's are in another language. If you can add Trigger words with Seaart I don't know how.

For this model I suggest using lavender skin & Gloria Sato in your prompts for this model. Euler a seems to be the best sampler since I used Cartunafied to train them. Lora weights used best around 0.8-1. Mess around with it and let me know what works best.

items.name: SDXL Food Icons
items.description:
That's a big LoRA! I know, I know...but I've been testing some settings and this is how big it came out. I trained a smaller version, but I felt like it was less 'creative' than the bigger one. But I will upload them for everyone to test out. All example images were generated using the bigger-sized LoRA. :)

This model was trained on 25 images of 1.5 generated images that I had been using for my Etsy shop. It got the style down perfect and thanks to SDXL it makes even more creative things. It was mainly trained on baked goods, but it can also do other food items. :)

While full strength works fine, I liked 0.7 strength the best for most things, but feel free to play with it!
